      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are two error reporting channels - the DSL catches some errors before handing them over to the compiler, and the compiler can also report its own errors (which we should then pick up on the DSL side of things and feed into the DSL error handler).\n\nThere have been a couple of times in the past where DSL error handling did not go according to plan, so I just hit it with a big hammer here to be absolutely 100% sure that we do not inadvertently fail this check despite encountering errors.\n\nBut now that you\u0027ve got me thinking more about this, I added an assert that will trip if we have compiler errors but haven\u0027t reported any errors on the DSL side, so we will at least catch this problem rather than silently ignore it.",
